  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main objective is to evaluate the interest of cerebro-splanchnic oxygenation ratio (CSOR)
      for early diagnosis of necrotizing enterocolitis (NEC) in neonates with rectal bleeding
      and/or abdominal distension. CSOR will be determined using near infrared spectroscopy (NIRS).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
